  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "ドクター・ワイリーがクロノス研究所に侵入し、タイムスキマーという機械を盗みました。ドクター・ライトの計算によれば、彼はその機械を使って約37,426年先の未来に旅をしたとのことです。これは良いことではなく、メガマンは犬のラッシュと共にドクター・ワイリーの計画についてもっと調べるために出発します。\n\nメガマンIIは前作と同じフォーミュラに従っており、プレイヤーはさまざまなボスに守られた横スクロールのプラットフォームレベルをクリアする必要があります。メガマンは左か右にしか撃てませんが、ボスを倒すことで新しい武器を手に入れることができます。また、時にはラッシュのアップグレードも見つかり、ラッシュをトランポリンや潜水艦、ジェットとして使用できるようになります。\n\nメガマンIIは移植版ではありませんが、最初の4つのステージはNES版メガマン2のいくつかのレベルに非常に似た見た目とプレイ感を持っています。同様に、5から8のレベルはメガマン3のいくつかのレベルに似ています。最初の8つのステージのボスも、メガマン2と3の古い顔ぶれです。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "The second handheld installment of the Mega Man series has him (along with his dog, Rush) defeating eight more revived Robot Masters (from Mega Man 2 and Mega Man 3), while finding the whereabouts of Dr. Wily (who has traveled into the future to steal a weapon to counter Mega Man).",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "Even after his crushing defeat at the hands of Mega Man during the events of Mega Man: Dr. Wily's Revenge, Dr. Wily was already planning his next scheme. If he could get his hands on the time machine (named Time Skimmer in the American manual) that was being developed at the Time-Space Research Laboratory (named Chronos Institute in the American manual), he thought he just might be able to change the past.\n\nAfter stealing the time machine, Wily had wanted to set out immediately on a trip across time, but had to put an emergency brake down on his plans when he discovered that the time machine had a serious flaw.\n\nMeanwhile, Dr. Light had been dispatched to the time-space laboratory to investigate. With the help of Rush’s super-sense of smell, he was able to deduce that it was none other than Dr. Wily behind the theft. Having a bad feeling about the incident, Dr. Light quickly called upon Mega Man and Rush to search out Dr. Wily’s whereabouts.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
